---
// Import your images and define staff data
import tctown from '@assets/twincities-downtown-acupuncture.webp';
import chadimg from '@assets/chad-dupuis-acupuncturist-yinyanghouse-twin-cities-acupuncture-280.webp';
---

<section id="aboutus" class="py-16 relative text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">
  <!-- Background Image -->
  <img
    src={tctown.src}
    alt="Twin Cities Downtown Background"
    class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover opacity-20"
  />
  <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 opacity-20"></div>

  <!-- Content Wrapper -->
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative z-10">
    <!-- About Us Section -->
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">About The Yin Yang House</h2>
    <p>
      The Yin Yang House Twin Cities Acupuncture and Wellness Center is the primary clinic of the Yin Yang House founder, Chad Dupuis.  The clinic strives to offer a wide range of services and educational/training opportunities to encourage long-term (and ideally self-maintained) health and wellness.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2">
      The Yin Yang House, through the various clinics and educational outreach arms, has been sharing the wealth of knowledge and techniques within Chinese Medicine and helping people since 1999.  We strive to offer best in class, common sense approaches to help people build and maintain their own health and wellbeing.
    </p>

    <!-- Our Staff Section -->
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-12">Founder / Practitioner</h3>
    <div class="bg-[#5cc4b5] dark:bg-[#3b8c82] text-white dark:text-gray-100 rounded-xl shadow-md p-8 max-w-xl mx-auto flex flex-col items-center">
      <img src={chadimg.src} alt="Chad Dupuis" class="w-32 h-32 rounded-xl object-cover mb-4" />
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 text-center">Chad Dupuis, L.Ac., Dipl.Ac.</h3>
      <p class="font-semibold mb-4 text-center">Acupuncturist / Owner</p>
      <div class="w-full">
        <p class="m-0">Chad has over 20 years of experience in helping people of all ages with nearly any set of of physical and/or mental health issues.  Voted the "<a href="https://gallery.bestofchatt.com/places/view/559/yin_yang_house_acupuncture_and_wellness_center.html">best of the best</a>" acupuncturist by his many thousands of patients, many years in a row, at the clinic he founded in <a href="https://yyhchattanooga.com/">Chattanooga</a> before he returned with his wife and two young boys to the midwest.</p>
        <br />
        <p class="m-0">He utilizes a range of techniques tailored to each individual patient, drawing heavily from the founder of Tong Ren Therapy, <a href="https://tongrenstation.com/uncategorized/tom-tam-bio/?sfw=pass1759177119">Master Tom Tam</a>, whom he has studied with, worked with, and continues to learn from for three decades.</p>
        <br />
        <p class="m-0">He is a perpetual student, prolific writer, and explorer who shares his knowledge freely through the <a href="https://yinyanghouse.com/">Yin Yang House</a> website.  His site has helped teachers, practitioners, and the general public alike explore the foundations and workings of Chinese Medicine and associated systems.</p>
        <br />
        <p class="m-0">He is also an avid meditator and qigong/tai chi practitioner who has studied and taught for over 30 years.  He offers classes utilizing these techniques to help his patients improve their health.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
</section>
